 South African President Cyril Ramaphosa was booed by the crowd in the stadium after a wave of deadly riots and xenophobic attacks in South Africa earlier this month that triggered international anger. The attacks mainly targeted shops owned by African migrants. The master of ceremony was forced to appeal to the crowd to give Ramaphosa a chance to speak. “I stand before you as a fellow African to express my regret and to apologize for what has happened in our country,” Ramaphosa said, to cheers from the crowd. Continue reading Xenophobia: Crowd booed South Africa’s President Ramaphosa at Mugabe’s funeral service at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard